      • executeGet

        public GuiUpdatedValue executeGet​(Object target,
                                  Object prevValue)
                           throws Exception
        execute the property method or obtain the value of the property field if target is null then nothing will happen and always return GuiUpdatedValue.NO_UPDATE.
        Parameters:
        target - the property holder
        prevValue - a previous value of the property, which can be compared to the new value and if it equals, the returned value will be GuiUpdatedValue.NO_UPDATE.
        Returns:
        the current property value or GuiUpdatedValue.NO_UPDATE if no difference from the prevValue
        Throws:
        Exception - it might be cause exception during the method invocation
